---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Suman Koirala" description="Background, approach, and the kind of projects I take on.">
	<section class="max-w-2xl">
		<h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-text dark:text-dark-text mb-8">
			About me
		</h1>

		<div class="space-y-5 text-text dark:text-dark-text leading-relaxed">
			<p>
				I'm Suman Koirala, an automation and systems consultant based in Kathmandu, Nepal.
				I work primarily with accounting firms — helping them stop doing repetitive work manually
				and start building systems that handle it for them.
			</p>

			<p>
				My toolkit includes Zapier, Make (formerly Integromat), Power Automate, Copilot Studio,
				Airtable, and Google Apps Script. The specific tool depends on the problem. I don't have
				a favorite — I have opinions about which ones work best in which situations, and those
				opinions come from building things that broke and figuring out why.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text dark:text-dark-text pt-4">How I work</h2>

			<p>
				I start by understanding the actual workflow — not the idealized version, but what people
				really do day-to-day. Then I figure out which parts can be automated without making the
				process more fragile. Not everything should be automated. The goal is fewer errors,
				less manual work, and systems that don't need constant babysitting.
			</p>

			<p>
				I document everything. If I get hit by a bus, whoever takes over should be able to
				understand the system from the docs alone.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text dark:text-dark-text pt-4">What I take on</h2>

			<p>
				Most of my projects fall into a few categories: client onboarding flows, document
				processing pipelines, CRM-to-accounting-software integrations, and internal workflow
				automation. If your accounting firm has a process that involves copying data between
				systems, sending follow-up emails manually, or maintaining spreadsheets that should
				update themselves — that's the kind of thing I fix.
			</p>

			<p>
				I also write about the work on this blog. Not "10 tips" content — actual implementation
				details, API problems I ran into, and how I solved them. If you're another implementer
				trying to solve a specific problem, you might find something useful here.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text dark:text-dark-text pt-4">Get in touch</h2>

			<p>
				If you want to talk about a project, the fastest way is email.
				Head over to the <a href="/contact/" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2 decoration-accent/40 hover:decoration-accent transition-colors">contact page</a> for details.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
